  "text": "The Java ClassLoader delegation chain involves the following key files:\n\n1. **src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java** — The base `ClassLoader` class. Defines the `loadClass(String name, boolean resolve)` method (around line 534) which implements parent-first delegation: it first delegates to the parent class loader, then searches itself if not found.\n\n2. **src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java** — Defines `BuiltinClassLoader` which extends `SecureClassLoader`. This is the base class for the three built-in class loaders (boot, platform, app). It uses a module-aware delegation model that can delegate to the application class loader even from the platform class loader for upgraded modules.\n\n3. **src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java** — Defines the `ClassLoaders` utility class that creates and provides access to the three built-in class loaders: `BootClassLoader` (BOOT_LOADER), `PlatformClassLoader` (PLATFORM_LOADER), and `AppClassLoader` (APP_LOADER). Exposes methods like `bootLoader()` and `platformClassLoader()`.\n\n4. **src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp** — The HotSpot C++ implementation of native class loading. This is the VM-level class loader that handles loading of class files from the boot class path and implements the low-level class file parsing and loading.\n\n5. **src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp** / **src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.cpp** — Defines the `SystemDictionary` class (`class SystemDictionary : AllStatic`). This is the VM-level cache/registry that stores loaded classes (keyed by name and class loader), preventing duplicate loading and enabling class resolution."
}

